<p>
<seg id="5">The economic systems directed to the liberalism, in the EU as well as in the context of the globalization, are based on the principle of more of not regulated economic competition.</seg>
<seg id="6">This means concretely that the different economic entities as the national economic systems are perpetually ones in conflict with the others.</seg>
<seg id="7">This results from the principle of the freedom of the business and of the free circulation (beyond measure) of the capital deprived ally to a frantic financial speculation.</seg>
<seg id="8">The sizeable differences of the price of the work (salaries) generate a tension on the prices.</seg>
<seg id="9">He admits to putting the next meaning under this term: a producer endeavors by the importation of goods sold down busy of resisting the economic competition "making more expensive" the price of the competitor, with the aim of taking off a greater part of the market and of increasing thus his own benefits.</seg>
