</p>
<p>
<seg id="55">Germany is not to it always accustomed, that is it always uncomfortable and, for evident reasons, the country has always difficulties to playing a more important role.</seg>
<seg id="56">If one looks, for example, at the crisis of the euro, one notices that to every time that Germany decides to weigh more, numerous anti-German feelings are made to hear.</seg>
