</p>
<p>
<seg id="61">Today, the influence of the United States on the European policy makes only to diminish, but at the moment, the EU does not fill in this space, then that it remains?</seg>
<seg id="62">The Germans will simply have to play a more important role.</seg>
<seg id="63">And even if that does not please them, even if that is them unpleasant and if they are only less appreciated it is the life!</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="64">Stephen Szabo is the manager assigned from the Transatlantic Academy of Washington, an institute in which academics and experts in policy of Europe and of North America analyze together the challenges of the transatlantic community.</seg>
<seg id="65">Szabo is also a member of the German Marshall Fund, where it has specialized in German policy, in American foreign policy and in transatlantic relationships.</seg>
